documentation.text:
@dev Liquidity Migrator contract to help migrating liquidity
       from other sources to Kyber DMM Pool
@dev Use only for some special tokens

@dev Allow the Owner to withdraw any funds that have been 'wrongly'
       transferred to the migrator contract
@dev Add liquidity to Kyber dmm pool, support adding to new pool or an existing pool
@dev Add liquidity to an existing pool, and return back tokens to users if any
@dev Add liquidity to a new pool, and return back tokens to users if any
@dev Re-write remove liquidity function from Uniswap
@dev only approve if the current allowance is 0
@dev Copy logic of sort token from Uniswap lib

@dev Liquidity Migrator contract to help migrating liquidity
       from other sources to Kyber DMM Pool
@dev Use only for some special tokens

@dev Allow the Owner to withdraw any funds that have been 'wrongly'
       transferred to the migrator contract
@dev Add liquidity to Kyber dmm pool, support adding to new pool or an existing pool
@dev Add liquidity to an existing pool, and return back tokens to users if any

devdoc.details: Liquidity Migrator contract to help migrating liquidity       from other sources to Kyber DMM Pool

manualApproveAllowance(address[],address.details: Use only for some special tokens

migrateLpToDmmPool(address,address,addre.details: Migrate tokens from a pair to a Kyber Dmm Pool with permit   User doesn't have to make an approve allowance transaction, just need to sign the data   Supporting both normal tokens and tokens with fee on transfer   Support create new pool with received tokens from removing, or       add tokens to a given pool address

params.amountAMin: min amount for tokenA when removing/adding
params.amountBMin: min amount for tokenB when removing/adding
params.deadline: only allow transaction to be executed before the deadline
params.liquidity: amount of LP tokens to migrate
params.poolInfo: info the the Kyber DMM Pool - (poolAddress, poolAmp)   if poolAddress is 0x0 -> create new pool with amp factor of poolAmp   otherwise add liquidity to poolAddress
params.uniPair: pair for token that user wants to migrate from   it should be compatible with UniswapPair's interface

migrateLpToDmmPoolWithPermit(address,add.details: Migrate tokens from a pair to a Kyber Dmm Pool   Supporting both normal tokens and tokens with fee on transfer   Support create new pool with received tokens from removing, or       add tokens to a given pool address

params.amountAMin: min amount for tokenA when removing/adding
params.amountBMin: min amount for tokenB when removing/adding
params.deadline: only allow transaction to be executed before the deadline
params.liquidity: amount of LP tokens to migrate
params.poolInfo: info the the Kyber DMM Pool - (poolAddress, poolAmp)   if poolAddress is 0x0 -> create new pool with amp factor of poolAmp   otherwise add liquidity to poolAddress
params.uniPair: pair for token that user wants to migrate from   it should be compatible with UniswapPair's interface

owner().details: Returns the address of the current owner.

renounceOwnership().details: Leaves the contract without owner. It will not be possible to call `onlyOwner` functions anymore. Can only be called by the current owner. NOTE: Renouncing ownership will leave the contract without an owner, thereby removing any functionality that is only available to the owner.

transferOwnership(address).details: Transfers ownership of the contract to a new account (`newOwner`). Can only be called by the current owner.

withdrawFund(address,uint256).details: Allow the Owner to withdraw any funds that have been 'wrongly'       transferred to the migrator contract
